become a precarious medium: whether in the context of climate change or global pandemic, space technology or gas warfare, air is now co-created and manipulated by humans. Against this backdrop, breath appears as an elusive yet vital substance that reveals the interconnections between the physical, symbolic, technological and social realms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aArt, Culture, History, Philosophy, Architecture.1 aBannehr, Pamela Britt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Marcus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlunck, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorchhardt, Kerstin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurchert, Linn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurchert, Linn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFischer, Ole W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox, Anselmo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGruber, Petra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuiducci, Lorenzo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHecht, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeßler, Annerose, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Dorothée, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorris, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOettl, Barbara, econtributor.4ct